Product Costing


  Cost of any cost object = direct costs + allocated
indirect costs. 
  Indirect costs are also called overhead, or common 
costs. 
  There is an arbitrarinessintroduced by the allocation
(or assignment) of common costs. 
  A product costing system is essentially an overhead
allocation system. 
  Costs are allocated to 
  products, 
  customers, and 
  departments within (or subunits of) the firm. 

