Product Costing


  Manufacturing overhead (MOH) includes 
  machine setup costs, 
  wages of forklift operator, 
  plant supervisor salaries, 
  manufacturing equipment depreciation, etc. 
  Non-manufacturing overhead (NMOH) includes indirect 
  marketing costs, 
  non-manufacturing administrative costs. 
  The costs allocated to a product will depend on the reason for 
the allocation: 
  under GAAP, only MOH is allocated in calculating inventory costs; 
  U.S. govt. cost-plus contracts explicitly exclude marketing 
overhead; 
  All overhead may be allocated for decision making (including 
pricing) and control. 

