Job Costing 


  Smooth overhead consumption, when activity varies, 
suggests that it is mainly fixed overhead. 
  We could also have allowed MOH to vary 
disproportionately in this case, e.g., 
  air conditioning costs may be higher in summer months, 
heating costs higher in winter, employee vacation pay will 
be higher in summer months, etc. 
  Takeaway: overhead rates should be calculated using 
longer period (e.g., annual) budgets, to reduce 
arbitrariness. 
  Identical jobs performed in different months should not 
differ in cost due to erratic costs or seasonal effects. 

