Manufacturing Cost Flows


  The third is finished goods (FG) inventory: 
  outflows from WIP increase it; 
  it is decreased by the cost of goods sold (COGS). 
  Finally, the COGS account (not an inventory 

account) is increased by outflows from FG.

  The ending balance of an inventory account  

is: beginning balance + inflows – outflows.


